com.mvohm.quadruple.test

Class DataProviders

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mvohm.quadruple.test.DataProviders

  • public class DataProviders
extends Object
    A collection of static methods that build and return data sets for testing different Quadruple operations.
    Each data set is a list of arrays of Strings. Each array represents a data sample to test the operation. It consists of two (for unary operations, including conversions) or three (for binary operations) strings that contain string representations of input operand(s) for the tested operation, and the expected result of the operation being applied to the given operand(s). For example, a data sample to test the addition may look like 
     {"2", "3", "5"}
    In most cases the expected result can be computed by the corresponding tester class, that uses the data returned by a provider. In such cases, a null or an empty string may be in place of the expected result value. For the above example it would look like 
     {"2", "3", ""}
    or 
     {"2", "3", null}

    A data sample from the list intended to test Quadruple.sqrt() may be 

     {"16.0", "4.0"}
    or just
     {"10000", null} // The expected value, 100, will be calculated by the tester class
    Each method collects a list of data samples for testing the corresponding operation as a concatenation of a statically defined array of data from the TestData class and one ore more data sets automatically generated by methods of the DataGenerators class.
    The statically defined data sets, specific for each tested operation, provide complete coverage of the code of the corresponding method of Quadruple, and may contain additional data to test some corner cases.
    Automatically generated data sequences are intended to test certain properties of tested operations, such as correctness of the rounding when converting a value from BigDecimal to Quadruple.
    Author:
    M.Vokhmentsev

      • q2sConversionDataList

        public static List<String[]> q2sConversionDataList()
        Assembles and returns a data set for testing the conversion from Quadruple to String. Includes subsets:
        • a number of values for rough testing of the corner cases, containing such values as NaN, Infinity, Double.MAX_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE, etc, and a few values between them;
        • Statically defined data set from TestData.basic_Q2S_conversionData that covers all execution paths of the tested method;
        • a sequence of a few adjacent values to see how the result changes when the input data changes by the least significant bit of the mantissa;
        • A series of sequences of adjacent values with various exponents to ascertain that multiplying by powers of two don't spoil the overall precision;
        • A number of random numbers.

        The returned data set is a list of arrays, each containing two strings -- an input value for the tested operation and the expected result, that can be null or an empty string.
        Returns:
        a set of data described above

      • q2dConversionDataList

        public static List<String[]> q2dConversionDataList()
        Assembles and returns a data set for testing the conversion from Quadruple to double. Includes subsets:
        • a number of values for rough testing of the corner cases, containing such values as NaN, Infinity, Double.MAX_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE, etc, and a few values between them;
        • Statically defined data set from TestData.basic_Q2D_conversionData that covers all execution paths of the tested method;
        • A number of random double values with added or subtracted half of the LSB of the Quadruple's mantissa, to ascertain that the rounding works right;
        • A number of random numbers.

        The returned data set is a list of arrays, each containing two strings -- an input value for the tested operation and the expected result, that can be null or an empty string.
        Returns:
        a set of data described above

      • s2qConversionDataList

        public static List<String[]> s2qConversionDataList()
        Assembles and returns a data set for testing the conversion from String to Quadruple. Includes subsets:
        • a number of values for rough testing of the corner cases, containing such values as NaN, Infinity, Double.MAX_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE, etc, and a few values between them;
        • basic data to test the conversion that covers all execution paths;
        • A number of random numbers;
        • A number of random values that differ from the corresponding Quadruple values by 0.5 LSB or 0.5 LSB * (1 - 2^-55), to ascertain that the rounding works right
        • A series of values near Quadruple.MIN_NORMAL : Quadruple.MIN_NORMAL + (Quadruple.MIN_VALUE * delta), where delta = -1.0 ... 1.0, with step 0.1;
        • A series of subnormal values, Quadruple.MIN_VALUE * (2^98 + delta), where delta = 9.0 ... 25.0, with step 0.5;,
        • A series of values of Quadruple.MIN_VALUE * (N + 0.5 +/- 3e-17), i.e close vicinities of subnormal values + 0.5 LSB, to test rounding down/up after computing subnormal values with diverse powers of 2;,
        • A series of values of (1 + Quadruple.MIN_VALUE * (N + 0.5 +/- 3e-17)) * 2^M, i.e close vicinities of normal values + 0.5 LSB, with various exponents, to test rounding down/up after multiplying the mantissa by diverse powers of 2;,

        The returned data set is a list of arrays, each containing two strings -- an input value for the tested operation and the expected result, that can be null or an empty string.
        Returns:
        a set of data described above

      • bd2qConversionDataList

        public static List<String[]> bd2qConversionDataList()
        Assembles and returns a data set for testing the conversion from BigDecimal to Quadruple. Includes subsets:
        • a number of values for rough testing of the corner cases, excluding the values that are not representable as BifDecimal
        • basic data to test the conversion that covers all execution paths;
        • A number of random numbers;
        • A number of random values that differ from the corresponding Quadruple values by 0.5 LSB or 0.5 LSB * (1 - 2^-128), to ascertain that the rounding works right
        • A series of values of Quadruple.MIN_VALUE * (N + 0.5) +/- 3e-40), i.e close vicinities of subnormal values + 0.5 LSB, to test rounding down/up after computing subnormal values with diverse powers of 2;,
        • A series of values of (1 + Quadruple.MIN_VALUE * (N + 0.5 +/- 3e-40)) * 2^M, i.e close vicinities of normal values + 0.5 LSB, with various exponents, to test rounding down/up after multiplying the mantissa by diverse powers of 2;,

        The returned data set is a list of arrays, each containing two strings -- an input value for the tested operation and the expected result, that can be null or an empty string.
        Returns:
        a set of data described above

      • additionDataList

        public static List<String[]> additionDataList()
        Assembles and returns a data set for testing addition. Includes subsets:
        • a number of pairs including all possible combinations of special values like -0, "NaN" and "Infinity" with each other and with some normal numeric values, to ascertain that initial checks in Quadruple.add() work right;
        • basic data to test the addition that covers all execution paths;
        • A number of pairs of random numbers.

        The returned data set is a list of arrays, each containing three strings -- two operands and the expected result, that can be null or an empty string.
        Returns:
        a set of data described above

        • A number of pairs of random numbers.

        The elements of the list are arrays, each containing three strings -- two operands and the expected result, that can be null or an empty string.
